g exposed to asbestos at armstrong gain access to trust funds grants and other forms of compensation for you or your loved ones get help now compensation for mesothelioma victims litigation  specific lawsuits armstrong’s asbestosrelated court battles began in the  landmark case of borel v fibreboard paper products corporation clarence borel sued armstrong and  other manufacturers of asbestos insulation after developing an asbestosrelated disease following his many years of working with their products this was the first case that recognized it was a manufacturer’s duty to warn of asbestos dangers and the case became the foundation for all future asbestos claims over the next few decades thousands of new asbestos claims were brought against armstrong and the company paid millions of dollars as courts ruled they knowingly disregarded the health of its employees and consumers by using asbestos in its products miller v armstrong world industries inc decided based on colorado law in  turned into a precedentsetting case for asbestos litigation raymond miller was an insulator from  to  and knowingly handled asbestos products from armstrong but he did not know asbestos was dangerous in his claim he said he learned of the dangers in the s while reading about asbestos miller developed asbestosis armstrong’s summary judgment victory was overturned on appeal the case set precedent under colorado law because it held that discovery of an initial asbestosrelated disease did not trigger the running of colorado’s statute of limitations on a separate disease that manifested later in this case for example the discovery of asbestosisrelated pleural thickening did not trigger the twoyear statute of limitations that would have prevented miller from filing an asbestosis claim by  the cost of asbestos litigation forced the company into bankruptcy as part of their emergence from bankruptcy and reorganization in  armstrong established the armstrong world industries asbestos trust which was intended to settle all current and future asbestosrelated claims in its first two years the trust received more than  claims industries  occupations armstrong favored asbestos because of its resistance to heat and insulating properties for much of its history the company included asbestos in insulation cements tiles vinyl flooring and many other products as a result such products placed a number of construction jobs at risk for exposure one of armstrong’s products was limpet a sprayon insulation made almost entirely of asbestos workers who tested limpet during its development in the s said it left too much dust in the air prompting the company to make an alternative product the inhalation of this dust was very hazardous and certainly placed employees at risk for developing an asbestosrelated disease later in life armstrong then began manufacturing armaspray a similar sprayon insulation made of only  percent asbestos testing of armaspray proved that it too was not commercially viable its production was discontinued within a year to finish ongoing projects however armaspray was used by armstrong installers for another year future health testing of the product concluded that dust levels were more than  times the limit deemed acceptable by company hygienists products armstrong employed a team of regular plant workers to manufacture products in general the company hired temporary workers to install insulation before the s both teams of workers came into direct contact with asbestos and were made susceptible to asbestosrelated diseases such as mesothelioma lung cancer and asbestosis the use of asbestosheavy sprayon insulation during the s made insulators especially vulnerable for future health problems asbestos use armstrong’s first asbestoscontaining products were released in the s with the hazards of asbestos well understood the company continued to manufacture and distribute asbestos products until the s executives failed to warn their employees about the dangers of asbestos and didn’t place warning labels on products containing the toxic mineral additional resources free mesothelioma information guide request yours now looking to file a lawsuit get help now free va claims help for veterans get help now free mesothelioma information guide find a mesothelioma attorney free va claims assistance section guide author matt mauney matt mauney is an awardwinning journalist with nearly a decade of professional writing experience he joined asbestoscom in  and he spends much of his time reading analyzing and reporting on mesothelioma research articles to ensure people in the mesothelioma community know the latest medical advancements prior to joining asbestoscom matt was a reporter at the orlando sentinel if you have a story idea for matt please email him at mmauneyasbestoscom view article sources rand  asbestos bankruptcy trusts an overview of trust structure and activity with detailed reports on the largest trusts retrieved from httpwwwrandorgpubstechnicalreportsrandtrpdf armstrong world industries  corporate history a historical summary retrieved from httpwwwarmstrongcom armstrong world industries welcome to the armstrong world industries asbestos trust retrieved from httpwwwarmstrongworldasbestostrustcom simpson pamela h cheap quick  easy imitative architectural materials  university of tennessee press  miller v armstrong industries inc united states court of appeals tenth circuit  nov  case no  retrieved from httpopenjuristorgfdmillervarmstrongworldindustriesincgaf share our page share tweet share view our resources for patients and families get help today get your free mesothelioma guide navigation mesothelioma finding treatment help for veterans legal options news about disclaimer faqs privacy policy blog monthly newsletter stay uptodate on treatment research clinical trials doctors and survivors sign up certifications this site complies with the honcode standard for trustworthy health information verify here connect with us sponsored