e it more competitive” mr lockhart said “we made substantial improvements in our cost structure by closing several plants and streamlining our workforce in the us we have also expanded capacity to manufacture wood flooring broadened our product lines and improved product quality and customer service” on march   armstrong world industries inc and npm capital nv entered into an agreement to sell tapijtfabriek h desseaux nv and its subsidiaries the principal operating companies in armstrong’s european textile and sports flooring business segment to npm capital nv the sale was finalized in april  on february   armstrong world industries inc announced that it was initiating a review of its strategic alternatives contents  history  armstrong manor  divisions  environmental record  manufacturing locations  references  external links historyedit former armstrong cork company building in pittsburgh pennsylvania built circa  in  thomas m armstrong the son of scottishirish immigrants from derry joined with john d glass to open a oneroom shop in pittsburgh pennsylvania carving bottle stoppers from cork by hand their first deliveries were made in a wheelbarrow armstrong was a business pioneer in some respects he branded each cork he shipped as early as  and soon was putting a written guarantee in each burlap bag of corks he shipped from his big new factory the company grew to be the largest cork supplier in the world by the s the company incorporated in  cork began being displaced by other closures but the company introduced insulating corkboard and brick in  two years before he died thomas armstrong concluded that the solid foundation of the future was covered with linoleum and construction began on a new factory in a cornfield at the edge of lancaster pennsylvania in  armstrong linoleum was first offered to the trade after corkboard the logical move was to fiberboard and then to ceiling board cork tile and linoleum led to vinyl flooring then ceramic tile laminate flooring and 